subject: Rajasthan History
question_en: Which Rajput clan ruled Jaipur from 1876 to 1947?
question_hi: जयपुर के बाजपुरी क्षत्रज्ञान 1876 तक 1947 तक संभाग को लागू करने वाले क्षत्रज्ञान क्या थे।
explanation_en: The Kachhwaha Rajputs were the rulers of Jaipur from 1876 to 1947. They belong to the Amber branch of the Kachhwaha clan. The Kachhwaha Rajputs were led by Maharaja Sawai Man Singh I and later by his grandson Maharaja Ram Singh II. They were the erstwhile rulers of Jaipur before the British established a direct rule over the city.
